{"type":"text","timestamp":1775881791121,"sessionID":"ses_28533d015ffeXLsSAJPeoBPyO8","part":{"id":"prt_d7acd1898001d3cwFBqgZgodzb","messageID":"msg_d7accfcd0001DnT9zUTwnVSbBS","sessionID":"ses_28533d015ffeXLsSAJPeoBPyO8","type":"text","text":"Now I have all the context needed. Let me write the proposal.md for AR-029:","time":{"start":1775881791117,"end":1775881791117}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775881791223,"sessionID":"ses_28533d015ffeXLsSAJPeoBPyO8","part":{"id":"prt_d7acda68f001PAGpcC8BDMOSJJ","messageID":"msg_d7accfcd0001DnT9zUTwnVSbBS","sessionID":"ses_28533d015ffeXLsSAJPeoBPyO8","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-a9832f5237f14436ad30d15fe9a2195f","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-029/proposal.md","content":"# AR-029 — SDK HTTP 底层客户端\n\n## 概述\n\n| 属性 | 值 |\n|------|-----|\n| AR | AR-029 |\n| Module | sdk-python |\n| Language | Python |\n| Size | M |\n\n---\n\n## 1. Purpose (目的)\n\nProvide the foundational HTTP client infrastructure for the AgentCube Python SDK. This module implements the low-level HTTP utilities that support all SDK client classes (`ControlPlaneClient`, `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient`, `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient`):\n\n1. `create_session()` — Creates a `requests.Session` with connection pooling via `HTTPAdapter` for both `http://` and `https://` protocols\n2. `read_token_from_file()` — Reads Kubernetes service account tokens from file paths, supporting in-cluster authentication\n3. `get_logger()` — Provides configured logger instances for SDK client logging\n\nThese utilities enable consistent HTTP session management, authentication token resolution, and logging across all SDK clients.\n\n---\n\n## 2. Scope (范围)\n\n### 2.1 In Scope\n\n- `agentcube/utils/http.py` — `create_session()` function:\n  - Configurable `pool_connections` (default: 10)\n  - Configurable `pool_maxsize` (default: 10)\n  - Mounts `HTTPAdapter` for both `http://` and `https://` schemes\n\n- `agentcube/utils/utils.py` — `read_token_from_file()` function:\n  - Reads file contents and strips whitespace\n  - Returns empty string on `FileNotFoundError` (graceful handling)\n  - Used by `ControlPlaneClient` to read SA token from `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token`\n\n- `agentcube/utils/log.py` — `get_logger()` function:\n  - Returns configured `logging.Logger` instance\n  - Supports both int and str level specifications\n  - Default level: `logging.INFO`\n\n- `agentcube/utils/__init__.py` — Module marker (empty)\n\n- Unit tests for all utility functions\n\n### 2.2 Out of Scope\n\n- HTTP request/response handling logic (handled by client classes)\n- Authentication header construction (handled by `ControlPlaneClient`)\n- Retry logic or circuit breaker patterns\n- Async HTTP support\n- SSL/TLS certificate configuration beyond defaults\n\n---\n\n## 3. Impact Analysis (影响分析)\n\n### 3.1 新增文件\n\n| File | Description |\n|------|-------------|\n| `sdk-python/agentcube/utils/http.py` | `create_session()` function for HTTP connection pooling |\n| `sdk-python/agentcube/utils/utils.py` | `read_token_from_file()` for token resolution |\n| `sdk-python/agentcube/utils/log.py` | `get_logger()` for logging configuration |\n| `sdk-python/agentcube/utils/__init__.py` | Empty module marker |\n| `sdk-python/tests/test_utils.py` | Unit tests for utils module |\n\n### 3.2 修改文件\n\n| File | Change |\n|------|--------|\n| N/A | No modifications required (pure addition) |\n\n### 3.3 Upstream Dependencies\n\n| Dependency | Purpose |\n|------------|---------|\n| `requests` | HTTP client library (core dependency) |\n| `requests.adapters.HTTPAdapter` | Connection pooling adapter |\n| `logging` | Standard library logging module |\n\n### 3.4 Downstream Consumers\n\n| Consumer | Usage |\n|----------|-------|\n| `agentcube/clients/control_plane.py` | Uses `create_session()` for HTTP session, `read_token_from_file()` for auth token |\n| `agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py` | Uses `create_session()` for HTTP session |\n| `agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py` | Uses `create_session()` for HTTP session |\n| `agentcube/code_interpreter.py` | Uses `get_logger()` for logging |\n| `agentcube/agent_runtime.py` | Uses `get_logger()` for logging |\n\n---\n\n## 4. Alternatives Considered (备选方案)\n\n### Alternative 1: Inline session creation in each client\n\nCreate `requests.Session()` directly in each client class without a shared utility.\n\n**Rejected:** Leads to code duplication. Connection pooling configuration would be scattered across multiple files. Shared utility ensures consistent HTTP behavior across all clients.\n\n### Alternative 2: Single Configuration class\n\nCreate a `Configuration` dataclass to hold all settings (base_url, timeout, pool settings, auth).\n\n**Rejected:** The design spec explicitly states \"no dedicated configuration dataclass\". Defaults are distributed across client constructors. Utility functions provide focused functionality.\n\n### Alternative 3: Use `httpx` instead of `requests`\n\nModern HTTP library with better async support and connection management.\n\n**Rejected:** `requests` is widely adopted, stable, and already listed as dependency. Adding `httpx` would increase complexity without clear benefit for synchronous SDK use case.\n\n### Alternative 4: Token reading with exception propagation\n\nLet `read_token_from_file()` propagate `FileNotFoundError` to caller.\n\n**Rejected:** Graceful empty string return enables optional authentication. `ControlPlaneClient` can proceed without token when running outside cluster. This pattern matches Kubernetes SDK conventions.\n\n---\n\n## 5. Risks\n\n| Risk | Mitigation |\n|------|------------|\n| Connection pool exhaustion under high load | Default pool size (10) is configurable; callers can adjust via `pool_connections`/`pool_maxsize` params |\n| Token file read permissions in container | Standard Kubernetes SA token path (`/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token`) has appropriate permissions |\n| Logger name collisions | Caller passes unique name string (e.g., `agentcube.code_interpreter`) |\n| Missing adapters for custom schemes | Only `http://` and `https://` are mounted; custom schemes not required for SDK use case |\n\n---\n\n## 6. Implementation Checklist\n\n- [ ] Implement `create_session()` in `agentcube/utils/http.py`\n- [ ] Implement `read_token_from_file()` in `agentcube/utils/utils.py`\n- [ ] Implement `get_logger()` in `agentcube/utils/log.py`\n- [ ] Create empty `agentcube/utils/__init__.py`\n- [ ] Write unit tests for `create_session()` (adapter verification)\n- [ ] Write unit tests for `read_token_from_file()` (success, file not found, whitespace handling)\n- [ ] Write unit tests for `get_logger()` (level configuration, name verification)\n- [ ] Verify pool configuration defaults match spec (10, 10)\n\n---\n\n## 7. References\n\n- python-sdk/design.md — AgentCube Python SDK design (utils section)\n- python-sdk/spec.md — SDK specification\n- `requests` documentation — HTTPAdapter and Session usage\n- Kubernetes in-cluster authentication — Service account token path convention"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/sdk-python/tests/test_utils.py":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/sdk-python/agentcube/utils/utils.py":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/sdk-python/agentcube/utils/http.py":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/sdk-python/agentcube/utils/log.py":[]},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-029/proposal.md","exists":true,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-029/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775881791197,"end":1775881791220}}}}
